<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
    <body>
        <h1>HTML Hyperlinks Demonstration</h1>
        <p>Hyperlinks in HTML are created using the <sub> < a > </sub> tag with the <sub> href </sub>attribute to specify the link
            destination. The <sub> target </sub> attribute determines how the link is opened.</p>
            <h2>Basic Hyperlink</h2>
            <p>Visit the <a href="https://www.google.com">Google</a> website. (Opens in the same tab.)</p>
            <h2>Open Link in a New Tab</h2>
            <p>Visit the <a href="https://www.wikipedia.com">Wikipedia</a> website. (Opens in the same tab.)</p>
            <h2>Open Link in Parent Frame</h2>
            <p> If this page is inside a frame, visit <a href="https://www.example.com">Example</a> in the parent frame.</p>
            <h2>Open Link in Full Window</h2>
            <p>Visit <a href="https://www.bbc.com">BBC News</a> to load in the full browser window.</p>
    </body>
</html>
